515/http://www.nextmagazine.com/content/bianca-del-rio-and-derek-saathoff-trade-barbs-lucas-entertainments-kings-new-york|archive-date=2013-10-15|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| Himself\n| Produced by [[Lucas Entertainment]]\n|-\n|2014\n|''Really Queen?''\n|Himself (in drag)\n|class=\"unsortable\" | Produced by WOW Presents\n|-\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Artist(s)\n! {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|2014\n|\"Sissy That Walk\"\n|RuPaul\n|\n|-\n|2014\n|\"Mean Gays\"\n|Courtney Act\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2015\n|\"This Is My Hair\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Alaska Thunderfuck\n|\n|-\n|\"Hieeee\"\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"Dance Like You Got Good Credit\"\n| Cazwell & Cherie Lily\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|\"Girly\"\n|John Duff\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.out.com/popnography/2018/8/24/exclusive-john-duff-gets-girly-channels-pop-icons-debut-video|title=Exclusive: John Duff Gets 'Girly,' Channels Pop Icons in Debut Video|last=Garner|first=Glenn|date=2018-08-24|website=Out.com|access-date=2020-03-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Theatre==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Theatre\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1998\n| ''[[Psycho Beach Party]]''\n| Marvel Ann\n| True Brew Theatre\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Papatola|first=Dominic P.|title=Cast had a ball, but 'Psycho Beach Party' must come to an end|url=http://www.nola.com/arts/index.ssf/1998/04/cast_had_a_ball_but_psycho_bea.html|work=[[The Times-Picayune]]|accessdate=24 October 2013|date=28 April 1998}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''At the Club Toot Sweet on Bourbon Street''\n| Cooch Deville\n| Southern Rep Theatre\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<ref name=\"stageclick\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''...And the Ball and All''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Ernesto\n| North Star Theatre\n|-\n| 1999\n| Southern Rep Theatre\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Cabaret (musical)|Cabaret]]''\n| Emcee\n| [[Le Petit Theatre du Vieux Carre]]\n| <ref name=\"stageclick\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2003\n| ''Bianca's Remote Out of Control''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Various roles\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Le Chat Noir\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Sands|first=Brian|title=Oh La La\u2013Cabaret as Art: Bianca's Remote Out Of Control at Le Chat Noir|url=http://www.ambushmag.com/is103/trod.htm|work=Ambush Magazine|accessdate=24 October 2013|year=2003|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029185745/http://www.ambushmag.com/is103/trod.htm|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Hollywood Heaven''\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Shannon|first=Patrick|title=Camping With The Black Cat, Again!: A Revisit to Hollywood Heaven and The Black & White Blues|url=http://www.ambushmag.com/is2603/trod.htm|work=Ambush Magazine|accessdate=24 October 2013|date=2003|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029195224/http://www.ambushmag.com/is2603/trod.htm|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2004\n| ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]''\n| Vince Fontaine\n| Le Petit Theatre du Vieux Carre\n| rowspan=\"7\"|<ref name=\"stageclick\">{{cite web|title=Roy Haylock|url=http://www.stageclick.com/person/725.aspx|work=StageClick|accessdate=24 October 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Murder at Movary Manor''\n| Daphne\n| Marigny Theatre\n|-\n| ''[[The Bad Seed (play)|The Bad Seed]]''\n| Hortense Daigle\n| Le Chat Noir\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2005\n| ''At the Club Toot Sweet on Bourbon Street''\n| Cooch Deville\n| rowspan=\"4\"|Le Petit Theatre du Vieux Carre\n|-\n| ''Pageant''\n| Miss Industrial Northeast<br />/ Tawny-Jo Johnson\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2008\n| ''Cabaret''\n| Emcee\n|-\n| ''[[Rent (musical)|Rent]]''\n| Angel Dumott Schunard\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2010\n| ''She'll Be Dying''\n| \n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Bowery Poetry Club]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=She'll Be Dying-2010|url=https://www.nytimes.com/theater/show/24571/She-ll-Be-Dying/overview|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=24 October 2013|year=2010}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Mayo on Your Breakfast at Tiffany's''\n| \n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Mayo on Your Breakfast at Tiffany's-2010|url=https://www.nytimes.com/theater/show/24756/Mayo-on-Your-Breakfast-at-Tiffany-s/overview|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=24 October 2013|year=2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Everybody's Talking About Jamie]]''\n|Hugo/Loco Chanelle \n|[[Apollo Theatre]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== Comedy tours ==\n* The Rolodex of Hate Tour (2014)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dragnearyou.com/tours/rolodex-of-hate/|title=Bianca Del Rio: The Rolodex Of Hate Tour - Drag Near You|last=info@dragnearyou.com|first=Drag Near You|website=Drag Near You|language=en|access-date=2018-06-15}}</ref>\n* Not Today Satan Tour (2016&ndash;2017)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theodysseyonline.com/not-today-satan-tour-review|title=Bianca Del Rio's Not Today Satan Tour Review|date=2016-10-04|work=The Odyssey Online|access-date=2018-06-15|language=en-us}}</ref>\n* [[Blame It On Bianca Del Rio Tour]] (2017-18)\n* It's Jester Joke Tour (2019)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" <!-- Do not center -->\n|- <!-- Never add unnecessary background colors -->\n! Year\n! Award Giving Body\n! Category\n! Work\n! Results\n! Ref.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|2020\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|[[Queerty|The Queerties]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Drag Royalty\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Herself\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.queerty.com/Queerties2020/|title='The 2020 Queerties|work=Cheat Sheet|date=February 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[LGBT culture in New York City]]\n* [[List of self-identified LGBTQ New Yorkers]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bianca Del Rio}}\n* {{Official website|http://thebiancadelrio.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|4081007|Roy Haylock}}\n* {{YouTube | id=jC01K5ZaNaU| title=Interview with Bianca Del Rio&nbsp;\u2014 RuPaul's Drag Race Season 6 }}\n* [http://www.newnownext.com/hurricane-bianca-trailer/08/2016 Trailer for 'Hurricane Bianca']\n\n{{RuPaul's Drag Race}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Del Rio, Bianca}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American costume designers]]\n\n[[Category:American people of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Honduran descent]]\n\n[[Category:Comedians from Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Gay actors]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American drag queens]]\n[[Category:LGBT comedians]]\n[[Category:LGBT Hispanic and Latino American people]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Louisiana]]\n[[Category:New York City nightlife]]\n[[Category:RuPaul's Drag Race winners|Bianca Del Rio]]\n[[Category:West Jefferson High School (Louisiana) alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Bianca Del Rio\n| image              = Bianca del Rio at Dragcon 2018 by dvsross.jpg\n| caption            = Del Rio in 2018\n| birth_name         = Roy R. Haylock\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1975|06|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]], U.S.\n| residence          = \n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = Drag queen, comedian, actor, costume designer\n| years_active       = 1993\u2013present\n| known_for          = ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'' [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 6)|(season 6)]] winner\n| predecessor        = [[Jinkx Monsoon]]\n| successor          = [[Violet Chachki]]\n| website            = {{URL|http://thebiancadelrio.com/}}\n| imagesize          = \n| restingplace       = \n}}\n\n'''Roy Haylock''' (born June 27, 1975), better known by the [[stage name]] '''Bianca Del Rio''', is an American [[drag queen]], comedian, actor, and costume designer best known for winning the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 6)|sixth season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''. In June 2019, ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine named Del Rio as the most powerful drag queen in America.<ref name=\"nymag\">{{cite news |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/most-powerful-drag-queens-in-america-ranked.html# |title=The Most Powerful Drag Queens in America: Ranking the new establishment. |author=The Editors |date=June 10, 2019 |access-date=June 10, 2019 |magazine=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |publisher=New York Media, LLC |archive-date=June 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610184458/https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/most-powerful-drag-queens-in-america-ranked.html |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nHaylock grew up in [[Gretna, Louisiana]]. He is of [[Cubans|Cuban]] descent on his mother's side and [[Hondurans|Honduran]] descent on his father's side.<ref>{{Citation|last=roscoestavern|title=Bianca's Roast LIVE at Roscoe's Tavern!|date=2014-08-30|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZCkJjrlImE|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref> He is the fourth of five children. He started acting and designing costumes for plays at [[West Jefferson High School (Louisiana)|West Jefferson High School]]. After high school, he decided to move to New York City, where he worked at [[Bloomingdale's]] for nine months before returning to Louisiana.<ref name=\"gambit\">{{cite web|last=Simmons|first=David Lee|title=Double Trouble|url=http://www.bestofneworleans.com/gambit/double-trouble/Content?oid=1240467|work=[[Gambit (newspaper)|Gambit]]|accessdate=24 October 2013|date=9 July 2002}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHaylock has primarily worked as a costume designer. In 1993, he won a Big Easy Entertainment Award for Best Costume Design for ''Snow Queen'' at the age of 17.<ref name=\"gambit\"/> He has been nominated for 13 Big Easy Entertainment Awards for costume design, winning six. Haylock has also made costumes for [[New Orleans Opera]].<ref name=\"cherrysonthebay\">{{cite web|title=Cherry's On The Bay\": Bianca Del Rio |url=http://cherrysonthebay.com/bianca_delrio.html |work=Cherry's On The Bay |accessdate=15 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131015080721/http://cherrysonthebay.com/bianca_delrio.html |archivedate=15 October 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn New Orleans, Haylock started performing as a drag artist in 1996 in the play ''Pageant''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreoli|first=Rick|title=Bianca Del Rio in 13|url=http://www.gay.net/entertainment/2010/09/bianca-del-rio-in-13.html|work=Gay.net|accessdate=14 October 2013|date=21 September 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017144653/http://www.gay.net/entertainment/2010/09/bianca-del-rio-in-13.html|archive-date=2013-10-17|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"getout\">{{cite web|last=C|first=Frankie|title=Frankie C Goes Head to Wig with The One & Only BIANCA DEL RIO|url=http://getoutmag.com/frankie-c-goes-head-to-wig-with-the-one-only-bianca-del-rio/|work=Get Out!|accessdate=14 October 2013|date=23 April 2012}}</ref> The local drag queen Lisa Beaumann saw him in the play and later cast him in shows at the nightclub Oz.<ref name=\"gambit\"/> Haylock won the New Orleans Gay Entertainer of the Year for three years as drag queen Bianca Del Rio.<ref name=\"cherrysonthebay\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Snap Paparazzi/Social Scene|url=http://www.ambushmag.com/is1504/snapx.htm|work=Ambush Mag|accessdate=15 October 2013|year=2004|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722102421/http://www.ambushmag.com/is1504/snapx.htm|archive-date=22 July 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, Bianca Del Rio was selected as co-grand marshal, with Pat \"Estelle\" Ritter and Rick Thomas for [[Southern Decadence]] XXIX.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Grand Marshals of Southern Decadence|url=http://www.southerndecadence.net/grand-marshal.htm|publisher=Southern Decadence|accessdate=20 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nHaylock moved to New York City after [[Hurricane Katrina]]<ref name=\"villagevoice\">{{cite web|title=Politically Incorrect Drag Insult Comic: \"I Hate People!\"|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/2012-07-04/columns/politically-incorrect-drag-insult-comic-i-hate-people/|work=[[Village Voice]]|accessdate=14 October 2013|author=Musto, Michael|date=4 July 2013|author-link=Michael Musto}}</ref> and worked as a costumer for Broadway shows, ballet and opera, having worked for [[Barbara Matera (costume designer)|Barbara Matera, Ltd.]]<ref name=\"getout\"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Montoya|first=Maria C|title=Actor/entertainer Roy Haylock returns to New Orleans for 'Rent'|url=http://blog.nola.com/davidcuthbert/2008/08/five_members_of_le_petit.html|work=[[The Times-Picayune]]|accessdate=24 October 2013|date=16 August 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029190421/http://blog.nola.com/davidcuthbert/2008/08/five_members_of_le_petit.html|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>  He also performed in drag as Bianca Del Rio, including in cabaret with [[Lady Bunny]] at XL Nightclub. Notable events included a roast of [[Patricia Krentcil]], better known as \"Tan Mom.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Hot Mess @ XL Nightclub|url=https://www.nextmagazine.com/content/gallery/hot-mess-xl-nightclub|work=[[Next Magazine (New York City)|Next]]|accessdate=15 October 2013|date=29 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015044930/https://www.nextmagazine.com/content/gallery/hot-mess-xl-nightclub|archive-date=15 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Cusma|first=Kathryn|title='Tan Mom' gets sloshed and thrown out of drag-queen show|url=https://nypost.com/2012/08/30/tan-mom-gets-sloshed-and-thrown-out-of-drag-queen-show/|work=[[New York Post]]|accessdate=15 October 2013|date=20 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nHaylock starred in the first regional production of ''[[Rent (musical)|Rent]]'' (following its initial Broadway closing) at Le Petit Theatre in New Orleans, playing the role of 'Angel' opposite [[Christopher Bentivegna]] as Collins.\n\nDel Rio was featured in the web series ''Queens of Drag: NYC'' by [[gay.com]] in 2010. The series featured fellow New York drag queens [[Dallas DuBois]], [[Hedda Lettuce]], [[Lady Bunny]], [[Mimi Imfurst]], [[Peppermint (drag queen)|Peppermint]], and [[Sherry Vine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gaycom launches Queens of Drag NYC|url=http://www.advocate.com/news/daily-news/2010/09/08/gaycom-launches-queens-drag-nyc|work=[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]|accessdate=14 October 2013|date=8 September 2010}}</ref> In 2011, Del Rio appeared on ''One Night Stand Up: Dragtastic! NYC'' by [[Logo TV]]. The episode was filmed live at the [[Bowery Ballroom]] and was hosted by [[Pandora Boxx]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Voss|first=Brandon|title=Hot Sheet Big Love, Idol, Skins|url=http://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/features/2011/01/14/hot-sheet-big-love-idol-skins|work=[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]|accessdate=14 October 2013|date=14 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Rupaul Dragcon 2018-42 (42030805642).jpg|thumb|left|Bianca Del Rio at RuPaul's DragCon LA, 2018]]\n\nHe appeared on the cover of ''[[Next Magazine (New York City)|Next]]'' for their Summer Yearbook 2012 issue.<ref>{{cite web|last=Avery|first=Dan|title=La Dolce Evita: Don't Cry For Drag Queen Bianca Del Rio|url=http://www.queerty.com/la-dolce-evita-dont-cry-for-drag-queen-bianca-del-rio-20120903/|work=[[Queerty]]|accessdate=15 October 2013|date=3 September 2012}}</ref> Del Rio appeared on the variety show ''[[She's Living for This]]'', hosted by [[Sherry Vine]], in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=WATCH: Tonight's 'She's Living For This' with Sherry Vine & Bianca Del Ro|url=http://www.gay.net/tv/2012/04/20/watch-tonights-she\u2019s-living-sherry-vine-bianca-del-rio|work=Gay.net|accessdate=19 October 2013|date=20 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120526120931/http://www.gay.net/tv/2012/04/20/watch-tonights-she%E2%80%99s-living-sherry-vine-bianca-del-rio|archive-date=2012-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2013, Logo announced that Bianca Del Rio was among 14 drag queens who would be competing on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 6)|sixth season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''. She quickly became a front-runner among the contestants and a fan favorite, eventually reaching the top three. On May 19, 2014, Del Rio was crowned the winner of the sixth season over runners-up [[Adore Delano]] and [[Courtney Act]]. She was the second winner and fourth contestant to reach the finale without having to [[lip sync]] for her life, and is the first and, to date, only contestant in the history of the series to make it through the entire competition without ever placing low or in the bottom of a challenge. Del Rio is also the first [[Hispanic]] winner of ''RuPaul's Drag Race''.\n\nIn 2013, Del Rio was announced as the lead in the independent film ''[[Hurricane Bianca]],'' written and directed by Matt Kugelman. An [[Indiegogo]] campaign was created to finance the film and was sponsored by [[Fractured Atlas]], a non-profit art services organization in New York City; the campaign raised over [[United States dollar|$]]30,000.<ref name=\"indiegogo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiegogo.com/projects/hurricane-bianca|title=Hurricane Bianca|last=Kugelman|first=Matt|work=[[Indiegogo]]|accessdate=15 October 2013}}</ref> A sequel, ''Hurricane Bianca: From Russia With Hate'', was released in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newnownext.com/hurricane-bianca-2-bianca-del-rio-katya-video/11/2017/|title=Bianca Del Rio Reveals What It Was Like Playing Katya's Lover In \"Hurricane Bianca 2\"|work=LOGO News|access-date=2018-02-08}}</ref>\n\nFollowing her success on ''Drag Race'', Del Rio has written and toured several stand-up shows, including ''The Rolodex of Hate'' (2014), ''Not Today Satan'' (2015\u201316), ''Blame It On Bianca Del Rio'' (2017\u20132018) and now, ''It's Jester Joke'' (2019) <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lamag.com/culturefiles/bianca-del-rio/|title=RuPaul's Drag Race Winner Bianca Del Rio Has Some Advice for You|date=2018-05-10|work=Los Angeles Magazine|access-date=2018-12-01|language=en-US}}</ref> , which also made her the first drag queen to headline [[Wembley Arena]]. She has also performed as a host on the [[Werq the World]] tour alongside other ''Drag Race'' queens.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nowtoronto.com/music/rupaul-s-drag-race-queens-werq-the-world-tour-in-photos/|title=RuPaul's Drag Race Queens Werq The World Tour: in photos|last=Ritche|first=Kevin|date=27 May 2017|work=Now Magazine|access-date=19 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Del Rio starred as retired drag queen Hugo Battersby/ Loco Chanelle in the hit West End musical [[Everybody's Talking About Jamie|Everybody\u2019s Talking About Jamie]]. In November that year, it was announced that he would reprise the role for 12 weeks starting 9th December.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''Cypress Edge''\n| \n| Assistant wardrobe\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''The Sons of Tennessee Williams''\n| Himself\n| Documentary\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''National Lampoon's Dirty Movie''\n| Drag Queen\n| Direct-to-video\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Hurricane Bianca]]'' <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/bianca-del-rios-upcoming-feature-length-comedy-wraps-filming-in-texas/08/2015/?xrs=synd_twitter_logo|title=Bianca Del Rio's Movie, \"Hurricane Bianca,\" Wraps Filming In Texas|work=NewNowNext|publisher=[[Logo TV]]|first=Adam|last=Salandra|date=August 9, 2015|accessdate=August 11, 2015}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Richard Martinez / Ms. Bianca Del Rio\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Hurricane Bianca: From Russia with Hate]]''\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''MTV Mardi Gras''\n| rowspan=\"12\"|Bianca Del Rio\n| TV Special\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2011\n| ''One Night Stand Up''\n| Episode 10: Dragtastic NYC\n|-\n| ''Threesome''<ref>{{cite web|title=Threesome Episodes&nbsp;\u2014 Threesome Full Episode Guides from Season 0 on Here! TV|url=http://www.tvguide.com/detail/tv-show.aspx?tvobjectid=348687&more=ucepisodelist&episodeid=22266277|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>\n| Season 1, Episode 3<br /> Season 1, Episode 4<br /> Season 1, Episode 14<br /> Season 1, Episode 15\n|-\n| ''[[Bad_Girls_Club_(season_7)|Bad Girls Club: New Orleans]]''\n| Season 7, Episode 5\n|-\n| 2012\u201313\n| ''[[She's Living for This]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=**She's Living For This**|url=http://www.heretv.com/sheslivingforthis/episodes/204.php|work=[[here TV]]|accessdate=24 October 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029194641/http://www.heretv.com/sheslivingforthis/episodes/204.php|archivedate=29 October 2013}}</ref>\n| Season 1, Episode 5: \"The Bianca Del Rio Episode\" <br /> Season 2, Episode 4\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 6)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n| 14 episodes, Winner\n|-\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 7)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n| Episode 7: \"[[Snatch Game]]\" (via video message)<br />Episode 13: \"Countdown To The Crown\"<br />Episode 14: \"Grand Finale\"\n|-\n|2015\n| ''[[List of Big Brother (UK) shows|Big Brother's Bit on the Side]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bigbrother.channel5.com/tonight-big-brothers-bit-side-17th-september|title=Tonight on Big Brother's Bit On The Side: 17th September|work=[[Celebrity Big Brother (UK TV series)|Celebrity Big Brother]]|publisher=[[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]]|date=September 17, 2015|accessdate=September 15, 2015}}</ref>\n| Celebrity panelist for the show on September 17, 2015\n|-\n|2016\n| ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 8)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n| Episode 9: \"The Realness\"\n|-\n|2016\n| ''Bianca's Rolodex of Hate''\n| 60-minute special of Bianca doing stand-up comedy, aired May 9, 2016 on Logo TV. The special was recorded in Austin, Texas.\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 2)|RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars]]''\n| Season 2, Episode 2: \"All Stars Snatch Game\" (via video message)\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 10)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n| Season 10, Episode 7: \"Snatch Game\" \n|-